  "title": "Indian Curry & Tandoor Chef",
  "description": "<p>Job Title: Indian Curry &amp; Tandoor Chef</p>\n<p>Location: East Region</p>\n<p>Working Hours: 6 days, 44 hours per week</p>\n<p>Salary: $4000 to $5000</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Job Responsibilities:</p>\n<p>* Prepare authentic Indian curries and manage the tandoor section (e.g. naan, tandoori meats, kebabs)</p>\n<p>* Ensure consistency and quality in all Indian dishes prepared</p>\n<p>* Coordinate with the kitchen team to ensure timely food preparation and service</p>\n<p>* Minimize food wastage and manage inventory efficiently</p>\n<p>* Assist in the creation of new Indian dishes and seasonal menus</p>\n<p>* Train and mentor junior kitchen staff in Indian cooking techniques and recipes</p>\n<p>* Ensure strict compliance with food safety, hygiene, and cleanliness standards</p>\n<p>* Maintain proper use and care of all tandoor equipment and cooking tools</p>\n<p>* Be flexible to assist in other sections of the kitchen when needed</p>\n<p>* Attend training sessions or meetings as scheduled</p>\n<p>* Carry out any other duties as assigned by the Head Chef or Management</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<p>* Minimum 3 years of experience in Indian curry and tandoor cooking</p>\n<p>* Strong understanding of Indian spices, herbs, and traditional cooking methods</p>\n<p>* Good communication and teamwork skills</p>\n<p>* Able to work in a fast-paced environment with attention to detail</p>",
